  "prompt": "How is the Culinary Institute of America for international students?",
  "response": "The Culinary Institute of America (CIA) is well-regarded for international students and offers several advantages:\n\n1. International student support:\n- Dedicated international admissions staff\n- Visa assistance\n- Cultural integration programs\n\n2. Global reputation\n- Internationally recognized culinary education\n- Highly respected worldwide in the hospitality industry\n\n3. Diverse student body\n- Students from many different countries\n- Multicultural learning environment\n- Opportunities to learn from global culinary perspectives\n\n4. Campuses\n- Multiple locations (New York, California, Texas, Singapore)\n- Singapore campus specifically caters to international students\n\n5. Programs\n- Associate and bachelor's degree options\n- Specialized culinary and baking programs\n- English language support\n\n6. Career opportunities\n- Strong industry connections\n- Internship programs\n- Optional Practical Training (OPT) for international students\n\n7. Potential challenges\n- Higher tuition costs\n- Competitive admission process\n- Need for strong English language skills\n\n8. Financial considerations\n- Scholarships available\n- Higher education expenses\n- Cost of living in campus locations\n\nInternational students should carefully research specific requirements, costs, and support services when considering the CIA.",
